#. <section class="sutta" id="sn5.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn5.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhunīvagga"
msgstr "1. Nuns"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn5.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Somāsutta"
msgstr "2. With Somā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.283"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn5.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho somā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the nun Somā robed up in the morning and, taking her bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn5.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena "
"andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya."
msgstr ""
"She wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on her return from alms-"
"round, she went to the Blind Man’s Wood,"

msgctxt "sn5.2:1.4"
msgid "Andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"plunged deep into it, and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "sn5.2:1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā somāya bhikkhuniyā bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ "
"uppādetukāmo samādhimhā cāvetukāmo yena somā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā somaṃ bhikkhuniṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the nun Somā feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, wanting to make her fall away from immersion, went up to her and "
"addressed her in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:2.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ taṃ isīhi pattabbaṃ,"
msgstr "“That state’s very challenging;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:2.2"
msgid "ṭhānaṃ durabhisambhavaṃ;"
msgstr "it’s for the sages to attain."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:2.3"
msgid "Na taṃ dvaṅgulapaññāya,"
msgstr "It isn’t possible for a woman,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:2.4"
msgid "sakkā pappotumitthiyā”ti."
msgstr "with her two-fingered wisdom.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho somāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the nun Somā thought:"

msgctxt "sn5.2:3.2"
msgid "“ko nu khvāyaṃ manusso vā amanusso vā gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Who’s speaking this verse, a human or a non-human?”"

msgctxt "sn5.2:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho somāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then she thought:"

msgctxt "sn5.2:3.4"
msgid ""
"“māro kho ayaṃ pāpimā mama bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo "
"samādhimhā cāvetukāmo gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This is Māra the Wicked, wanting to make me feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, wanting to make me fall away from immersion!”"

msgctxt "sn5.2:3.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho somā bhikkhunī “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ "
"gāthāhi paccabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Somā, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.284"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:4.1"
msgid "“Itthibhāvo kiṃ kayirā,"
msgstr "“What difference does womanhood make"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:4.2"
msgid "cittamhi susamāhite;"
msgstr "when the mind is serene,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:4.3"
msgid "Ñāṇamhi vattamānamhi,"
msgstr "and knowledge is present"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:4.4"
msgid "sammā dhammaṃ vipassato."
msgstr "as you rightly discern the Dhamma."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:5.1"
msgid "Yassa nūna siyā evaṃ,"
msgstr "Surely someone who might think:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:5.2"
msgid "Itthāhaṃ purisoti vā;"
msgstr "‘I am woman’, or ‘I am man’,"

# Reading asmīti with other translators. But surely the Upanishadic echoes should be preserved here; it gets lost if we abbreviate “I’m”. She’s not just dismissing other conceptions of ultimate gender identity, but even the supposed post-gender Upanishadic self.
#. <br>
#. VAR: aññasmi → aññasmiṃ (bj) | asmīti (s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn5.2:5.3"
msgid "Kiñci vā pana aññasmi,"
msgstr "or ‘I am’ anything at all,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.2:5.4"
msgid "Taṃ māro vattumarahatī”ti."
msgstr "is fit for Māra to address.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.2:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ somā bhikkhunī”ti dukkhī dummano "
"tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Somā knows me!” miserable and sad, "
"vanished right there."
